HEADWORD: Unparadise
<hw>Un*par"a*dise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>paradise</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of
happiness like that of paradise; to render unhappy.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unparagoned</ent>⟦br⟧
